{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idcb81f681-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s32709"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"32709"},"text":"§ 32709.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Penalties and enforcement","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idcb81f682-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s32709/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Civil Penalty","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idcb81f683-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s32709/a/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" A person that violates this chapter or a regulation prescribed or order issued under this chapter is liable to the United States Government for a civil penalty of not more than $10,000 for each violation. A separate violation occurs for each motor vehicle or device involved in the violation. The maximum penalty under this subsection for a related series of violations is $1,000,000.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idcb81f684-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s32709/a/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The Secretary of Transportation shall impose a civil penalty under this subsection. The Attorney General shall bring a civil action to collect the penalty. Before referring a penalty claim to the Attorney General, the Secretary may compromise the amount of the penalty. Before compromising the amount of the penalty, the Secretary shall give the person charged with a violation an opportunity to establish that the violation did not occur.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idcb81f685-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s32709/a/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" In determining the amount of a civil penalty under this subsection, the Secretary shall consider—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idcb81f686-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s32709/a/3/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the nature, circumstances, extent, and gravity of the violation;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idcb81f687-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s32709/a/3/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" with respect to the violator, the degree of culpability, any history of prior violations, the ability to pay, and any effect on the ability to continue doing business; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idcb81f688-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s32709/a/3/C"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"C"},"text":"(C)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" other matters that justice requires.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idcb81f689-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s32709/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Criminal Penalty","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"A person that knowingly and willfully violates this chapter or a regulation prescribed or order issued under this chapter shall be fined under title 18, imprisoned for not more than 3 years, or both. If the person is a corporation, the penalties of this subsection also apply to a director, officer, or individual agent of a corporation who knowingly and willfully authorizes, orders, or performs an act in violation of this chapter or a regulation prescribed or order issued under this chapter without regard to penalties imposed on the corporation.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idcb81f68a-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s32709/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Civil Actions by Attorney General","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"The Attorney General may bring a civil action to enjoin a violation of this chapter or a regulation prescribed or order issued under this chapter. The action may be brought in the United States district court for the judicial district in which the violation occurred or the defendant is found, resides, or does business. Process in the action may be served in any other judicial district in which the defendant resides or is found. A subpena for a witness in the action may be served in any judicial district.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idcb81f68b-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s32709/d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"d"},"text":"(d)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Civil Actions by States","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idcb81f68c-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s32709/d/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" When a person violates this chapter or a regulation prescribed or order issued under this chapter, the chief law enforcement officer of the State in which the violation occurs may bring a civil action—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idcb81f68d-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s32709/d/1/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" to enjoin the violation; or","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idcb81f68e-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s32709/d/1/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" to recover amounts for which the person is liable under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t49/s32710"},"text":"section 32710 of this title","children":[],"tail":" for each person on whose behalf the action is brought."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idcb81f68f-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s32709/d/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" An action under this subsection may be brought in an appropriate United States district court or in a State court of competent jurisdiction. The action must be brought not later than 2 years after the claim accrues.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idcb81f690-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/272/s1/e"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–272, § 1(e)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1994-07-05"},"text":"July 5, 1994","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/108/1054"},"text":"108 Stat. 1054","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/141/dC/tI/s31206/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 112–141, div. C, title I, § 31206(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2012-07-06"},"text":"July 6, 2012","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/126/761"},"text":"126 Stat. 761","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idcb81f691-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"historicalAndRevision","id":"idcb81f692-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:table","attrib":{"width":"50%","id":"idcb81f693-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:colgroup","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:col","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:col","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:col","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:thead","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:th","attrib":{"colspan":"3"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"Historical and Revision Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:th","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:i","attrib":{},"text":"Revised","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:i","attrib":{},"text":"Section","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:th","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:i","attrib":{},"text":"Source (U.S. Code)","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:th","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:i","attrib":{},"text":"Source (Statutes at Large)","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:tbody","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"32709(a)","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":"15:1988(b) (related to violating rules).","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"Oct. 20, 1972","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/92/513/s408/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 92–513, § 408(b)","children":[],"tail":" (related to violating rules), "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/86/963"},"text":"86 Stat. 963","children":[],"tail":"; restated "},{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"July 14, 1976","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/364/s406"},"text":"Pub. L. 94–364, § 406","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/90/983"},"text":"90 Stat. 983","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":"15:1990b.","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"Oct. 20, 1972","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/92/513"},"text":"Pub. L. 92–513","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/86/947"},"text":"86 Stat. 947","children":[],"tail":", §§ 412, 413; added "},{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"July 14, 1976","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/364/s408/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 94–364, § 408(2)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/90/984"},"text":"90 Stat. 984","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"Oct. 28, 1986","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/579/s3"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–579, § 3","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/100/3311"},"text":"100 Stat. 3311","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"32709(b)","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":"15:1988(b) (related to violating rules).","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":"15:1990c.","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"32709(c)","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":"15:1990.","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"Oct. 20, 1972","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/92/513/s410"},"text":"Pub. L. 92–513, § 410","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/86/963"},"text":"86 Stat. 963","children":[],"tail":"; restated "},{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"July 14, 1976","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/364/s407"},"text":"Pub. L. 94–364, § 407","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/90/984"},"text":"90 Stat. 984","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"32709(d)","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":"15:1990a.","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"Oct. 20, 1972","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/92/513"},"text":"Pub. L. 92–513","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/86/947"},"text":"86 Stat. 947","children":[],"tail":", § 411; added "},{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"July 14, 1976","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/364/s408/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 94–364, § 408(2)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/90/984"},"text":"90 Stat. 984","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (a)(1), the words “that violates this chapter” are substituted for “who commits any act or causes to be done any act that violates any provision of this subchapter or omits to do any act or causes to be omitted any act that is required by any such provision” in 15:1990b(a) for consistency and to eliminate unnecessary words. The words “or a regulation prescribed or order issued under this chapter” are substituted for “No transferor shall violate any rule prescribed under this section” in 15:1988 for consistency in the revised title and because “rule” is synonymous with “regulations”. The words “A separate violation occurs for each motor vehicle or device involved in the violation” are substituted for “A violation of any such provision shall, for purposes of this section, constitute a separate violation with respect to each motor vehicle or device involved” in 15:1990b(a) to eliminate unnecessary words.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (a)(2), the words “on behalf of the United States” are omitted as surplus. The words “Before compromising the amount of a penalty, the Secretary shall give” are substituted for “after affording” for clarity. The words “to present views and evidence in support thereof” and “alleged” are omitted as surplus.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (b), the words “that knowingly and willfully violates this chapter” are substituted for “knowingly and willfully commits any act or causes to be done any act that violates any provision of this subchapter or knowingly and willfully omits to do any act or causes to be omitted any act that is required by such provision” to eliminate unnecessary words. The words “or a regulation prescribed or order issued under this chapter” are substituted for “No transferor shall violate any rule prescribed under this section” in 15:1988 for consistency in the revised title and because “rule” is synonymous with “regulation”. The words “fined under title 18” are substituted for “fined not more than $50,000” for consistency with title 18. The words “an act in violation of” are substituted for “any of the acts or practices constituting in whole or in part a violation of” to eliminate unnecessary words.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsections (c) and (d), the word “enjoin” is substituted for “restrain” for consistency.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (c), the words “The United States district courts shall have jurisdiction” are omitted because of 28:1331. The words “for cause shown and subject to the provisions of rule 65(a) and (b) of the Federal Rules of Civil Procedure” are omitted as surplus because the rules apply in the absence of an exemption from them. The words “the violation occurred” are substituted for “wherein any act, omission, or transaction constituting the violation occurred”, and the word “resides” is substituted for “is an inhabitant”, to eliminate unnecessary words. The words “may be served in” are substituted for “may run into” for clarity.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (d)(1), before clause (A), the words “this chapter or a regulation prescribed or order issued under this chapter” are substituted for “requirement imposed under this subchapter” for consistency. The words “civil action” are substituted for “any action” for consistency with rule 2 of the Federal Rules of Civil Procedure (28 App. U.S.C.).","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (d)(2), the words “without regard to the amount in controversy” are omitted because jurisdiction is now allowed under 28:1331 without regard to the amount in controversy. The words “United States district court” are substituted for “district court of the United States” for consistency with the definition in section 32101 of the revised title and with other provisions of the chapter.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idcb81f694-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idcb81f695-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2012—Subsec. (a)(1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/141"},"text":"Pub. L. 112–141","children":[],"tail":" substituted “$10,000” for “$2,000” and “$1,000,000” for “$100,000”."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idcb81f696-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"idcb81f697-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 2012 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/141"},"text":"Pub. L. 112–141","children":[],"tail":" effective "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2012-10-01"},"text":"Oct. 1, 2012","children":[],"tail":", see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/141/s3/a"},"text":"section 3(a) of Pub. L. 112–141","children":[],"tail":", set out as an Effective and Termination Dates of 2012 Amendment note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t23/s101"},"text":"section 101 of Title 23","children":[],"tail":", Highways."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
